INSTRUCTION MANUALS DIGITAL

    BENEFITS OF DIGITAL INSTRUCTION MANUALS

  • It Helps To Extend The Product Information Provided To The Customer Through Images, Instructions And Audio Resources, As Well As Synthesizing It In A Way That Allows The User To Have An Interactive Experience

  • It Can Be Implemented On The Customer's Page So That The End User Can Interact Directly With The Product Even Long Before He Has It As An Acquisition And Thus Can Be An Advertising Link For The Products And Services That The Customer Has On His Page And Can Indirectly Incentive The Customer To Be Able To Interact With More Products And Services

  • It Has The Facility Of Reducing Costs, This In Order To Be Able To Reduce The Different Costs Required By A Traditional Instruction Manual, And It Is An Unlimited Way Of Being Able To Provide Any Type Of Customer With This Information, Whether At A National Or International Level

  • It Is Adaptable To Different Type Of Device, Whether Tablets, Pc, Cell Phones, It Is Also Reeditable So If You Want To Add, Correct Or Remove Any Information Component, It Can Be Done During The Implementation Until The Client Requires It

  • The Translation Of The Digital Reading Manuals Will Be Done According To The Translation Implemented By The Same Browser According To How You Want It

SCREWS SUPPORTS

    DIMENSIONS THE PIECES SCREWS BLACK

  • LARGUE:1 CM
  • WIDTH: 8 MM
  • MATERIAL: WOOD SCREW FOR REINFORCEMENT SQUADS

STEPS FOR TO INSTALL

  1. TO PUT SUPPORT ANGLE IN ORDEN AND INLINE 20 CENTIMETERS BETWEEN SUPPORTS OF MANNER CENTRED AT THE SPACE OF THE DIVISION THIS IN THE SIDE LEFT AND SIDE RIGHT WITH HEIGHT OF THE 23.5 CENTIMETERS
  2. TO PUT SCREWS SUPPORTS IN STRUCTURE WITH SUPPORT, THIS COULD TO PUT THE DIVISION HORIZONTAL WITHOUTH SCREW AS PREFERENCE, IF YOU WISH TO LEAVE THE SUPPORT FIXED IN THE HORIZONTAL DIVISION, FIRST PLACE THE SUPPORT TO THE DIVISION AND THEN TO THE STRUCTURE
  3. TO INSTALL SCREWS IN EACH THE HOLES UNTIL THAT SCREW STAY INSIDE SUPERFACE WOOD

  2. MAKING THE HOLES(3 HOLES) WITH A #8 MM COUNTERSINK DRILL BIT IN THIS CASE EQUAL THICKNESS OF THE SCREW
  3. TO INSTALL SCREWS IN EACH THE HOLES UNTIL THAT SCREW STAY INSIDE SUPERFACE WOOD

SUPPORT-FORNITURE-PROCESS

    DIMENSIONS THE PIECES SCREWS BLACK

  • LARGUE:4 CM
  • WIDTH: 8 MM
  • MATERIAL: WOOD SCREW FOR STRUCTURE ASSEMBLY

STEPS FOR TO INSTALL

  1. MAKING THE HOLES (5 HOLES) IN THE SUPPORT HALF VERTICAL 7 POINT 5 WITH A #8 MM COUNTERSINK DRILL BIT IN THIS CASE EQUAL THICKNESS OF THE SCREW
  2. CALCULATE THAT THE SCREW ADHERES TO THE VERTICAL DIVISIONS, THIS IN ORDER TO REMAIN THE SUPPORT FIXED TO THE TRIPLEX AND THE STRUCTURE
  3. TO INSTALL SCREWS IN EACH THE HOLES UNTIL THAT SCREW STAY INSIDE SUPERFACE WOOD

SUPPORT WALL PROCESS

IN PREFERENCE TO MAKE THIS PROCESS IN SUPERIOR PART OF THE WALL KITCHEN OR THE PREFERENCE PLACE

    DIMENSIONS THE PIECE TOP

  • LARGUE:5 CM
  • WIDTH: 3/4 INCHES
  • MATERIAL: STEEL

STEPS FOR TO INSTALL

  1. MAKING THE HOLES (3 HOLES) IN THE SUPPORT HORIZONTAL AND IT HAS 71.5 CENTIMETERS BETWEEN HOLE WITH A #3/4 INCHES FOR THE EXPANSIVE SCREW COUNTERSINK DRILL BIT IN THIS CASE EQUAL THICKNESS OF THE SCREW OF EXPANSIVE SCREW
  2. WITH A MARKER TO POINT THROUGH HOLES AT THE WALL THE POINTS FOR TO DRILL THE WALL AND TO INSERT
  3. THE MEASURES FOR TO DRIL IS OF ¾ AND FOR THE THREE EXPANSION SCREW OF SELF MEASURES ¾ WITH MEASURE OF THE DEEP OF THE 5 CENTIMETERS
  4. INSERT THE EXPANSION SCRE IN THE HOLES, TO PUT THE SUPPORT WALL IN THE WALL, NEXT INSERT THE SCREW IN THE HOLE OF THE SUPPORT WALL
